default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default9.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultShould the government take any further any specific actions in relation to cooling?default&#xa0;
defaultThe priority for policymakers should be on reducing heat demand, rather than focusing on cooling. 
defaultIt is of course right to be concerned with making cooling technologies as efficient and low carbon as possible, but with the current trajectory for low carbon and energy efficient heating being a key concern, it is important that policy and delivery remain
defaults focused on these technologies in order to meet legally binding emissions reduction and renewables targets.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is sensible, however, to ensure that cooling and ventilation issues remain part of the debate about the heating market as it develops over the 
defaultcoming years. It is sensible, for instance, that policy makers consider ventilation technologies as part of an energy efficiency strategy which will drive the installation of insulation, draught proofing and so on into retrofit properties. It is important 
defaultto ensure that properties are thermally efficiency and do not over-heat when temperatures are high, as they have been in 
defaultsummer
default 2013. Ventilation may well be part of such solutions.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe air conditioning market is being pushed hard to increase efficiency t
defaulthrough the European Directive on Energy Using Products
default 
defaultThis 
defaultD
defaultirective will encourage increased energy efficiency through innovation and development
default of technologies
default. Products which recover heat from server rooms, move heat build-up around buildings and reco
defaultver heat from hot water are already in existence.
default 
defaultSuch technologies
default are 
defaultalso 
defaultwell developed in harvesting heat from the ground and air
default,
default 
defaultknown respectively as “ground source” and “air source”
default&#xa0;
defaultThe government should be wary of 
defaulttechnologies which simply deliv
defaulter 
default‘
defaultactive cooling
default’
default such as ground to water heat 
defaultpumps, which
default are pitched as increasing the efficiency of the heating element over the course of seasons.
default A better way of increasing the heating efficiency over seasons is to use passive cooling (cool water s
defaulttraight from the ground)
default. I
defaultn
default order to take advantage of the cooling properties of water pumped straight from the ground, heat emmitters would need to be sized bigger. However the process uses very little electrical energy (just the pump). 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe RHI currently supports heating-only technologies, and we support this 
defaultas a policy principle because it is
default this market that needs stimulus for growth
default. Much more independent analysis would need to be performed on heating and cooling systems before it wou
defaultld be wise to consider it as a genuine policy solution. 
